Alo Moves × Difficulty & Intensity Guide This comprehensive guide will help you find which series is right for you Difficulty Levels Difficulty refers to the level of skill and technique called for in a Difficulty—Beginner—Outlined Copy Created with Beginner Beginner series are most approachable for those who have little or no exposure to These series typically offer more modifications and detailed instructions on fundamental These series are perfect for someone who is looking to start a yoga practice and explore the benefits of These classes can help you to learn the basics of starting a practice, foundational poses, understanding breathwork, and learning to focus on the moment every time you come to the Read more Close Difficulty—Moderate—Outlined Copy Created with Moderate Moderate classes may include moderate pose modifications and less instruction than found in Beginner These series are perfect for someone who has previous exposure to yoga, whether at home or in a studio setting, and has a basic understanding of foundational poses and class They are the perfect opportunity to grow your practice, maintain consistency, and enjoy classes designed to grow your pose library and increase your Read more Close Difficulty—Intermediate—Outlined Copy Created with Intermediate Intermediate series tend to be more detailed tutorials on how to achieve more challenging asanas and These classes help build strength and body awareness by exploring transitions, trying inversions, and mastering breath and These series are perfect for someone who has a consistent yoga practice and has established confidence in poses, progressions, and general yoga They help students express creativity and find freedom in exploring flows and There is less cueing than in Beginner or Moderate Read more Close Difficulty—Advanced Copy Created with Advanced Advanced classes are the perfect opportunity to explore your potential beyond what is found in typical Yo
